{
  "texts": [
    "The sensor was attached to a specific part of the body, which restricted data collection to that particular area.",
    "As a result, we were unable to obtain a comprehensive understanding of the mechanics of badminton strokes across the entire body.",
    "For instance, the use of wearable sensors in this study was limited by the number of available sensors, and as a result, EMG sensors were only attached to the dominant arm and foot.",
    "Moreover, the discomfort associated with wearing multiple sensors can affect the accuracy of badminton stroke data.",
    "This is a significant limitation of wearable sensors that needs to be addressed."
  ]
}